
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates the use of the [add] slot to append nodes to a collection. It retrieves nodes specified by expressions pointing to arguments named [order], [direction], [limit], and [offset] using [get-nodes], and appends these nodes to the collection referenced by [data.read]. The [add] slot is used to modify the structure of the node graph by adding new nodes to a specified location.
add:x:./*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/order
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/direction
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/limit
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/offset
